YOUR MISSION

We are hiring within the Platform cluster in the Infrastructure Runtime team at Glovo, responsible for building and scaling the foundations enabling engineering velocity, system reliability, and platform resilience.

We are looking for a Senior Platform Engineer who will raise the bar at a company level, leading cross-team initiatives, serving as a technical reference in the Infrastructure domain, and mentoring engineers while shaping our Kubernetes, GitOps, and CI/CD platform strategies.

THE JOURNEY

Contribute to technical projects that evolve our Kubernetes-based compute platform on AWS, with a focus on reliability, scalability, and developer productivity.
Help iterate on our GitOps workflows using Argo CD and Argo Rollouts for safe, automated, and progressive deployments.
Improve CI/CD best practices by building and maintaining scalable GitHub Actions pipelines.
Implement and enhance secure, multi-tenant infrastructure using Infrastructure as Code (Terraform).
Solve challenging problems in distributed systems, service discovery, container orchestration, and platform observability.
Take ownership of critical compute and networking infrastructure to ensure high performance, availability, and cost efficiency.
Build and maintain internal tooling and automation scripts using Go and Python.
Ensure our systems remain robust, reliable, and support smooth business operations.
Collaborate with platform and product engineers to propagate best practices and platform knowledge.
Share learnings with the team through documentation, pairing, and technical discussions.

What You Will Bring To The Ride

3+ years of relevant infrastructure experience, ideally in a platform team.
Solid experience with Kubernetes internals, observability, and cloud-native architecture (EKS a plus).
Programming proficiency in Golang
Hands-on experience with AWS services (EC2, S3, IAM, VPC, etc.) and Terraform.
Familiarity with GitOps principles and tooling (Argo CD, Argo Rollouts, or similar).
Good understanding of CI/CD systems (GitHub Actions or similar).
Networking and security knowledge (VPCs, DNS, ingress, TLS, etc.).
Experience working on technical projects and collaborating across teams.
Ability to analyze and improve performance and cost efficiency of distributed systems.
Awareness of event-driven architectures and reliability engineering practices.
Strong written and verbal communication skills in English.

Individuals representing diverse profiles, encompassing various genders, ethnicities, and backgrounds, are less likely to apply for this role if they do not possess solid experience in 100% of these areas. Even if it seems you don't meet our musts don't let it stop you, we are all about finding the best talent out there! Skills can be learned, and embracing diversity is invaluable.

